'''Actual development level''' refers to how much a child can achieve independently without the assistance of a [[parent]]s, [[teacher]]s, or [[peer group|peer]]s.<ref name="Tzuriel">{{cite book|last=Tzuriel|first=David|title=Dynamic Assessment of Young Children|publisher=Springer|date=2001-09-15|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UOMqoEyV0BoC&pg=PA13&dq=%22Actual+development+level%22&lr=&as_brr=3&ei=cJBSSJyxEp_otQO8oazAAw&sig=EXiw0TdWq0VrIgIQCe1OWYj1zGU|page=13}}</ref>

